The paper deals with distributed computation by mobile robots in a spatial universe, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus on graphs and their properties suggests a connection to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS). The use of mobile robots and their movements in the universe suggests a connection to Robotics (cs.RO). The investigation of which functions can be computed by the robots suggests a connection to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Finally, the approximation of the minimum size of the network suggests a connection to Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
